<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-09T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-09T11:00:00-05:00" n="880" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d880">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/11564: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Second Secretary of Embassy in China</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-10T00:00:00+08:00">December 10,
                                        1937—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received December 10—3:15
                                    p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1032. International Committee requests that following be communicated
                                as soon as possible to Japanese Embassy: <pb facs="0795" n="788" xml:id="pg_788"/>
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>“International Committee, Nanking, for sake of 200,000
                                        civilians, seeks prompt and favorable reply to yesterday’s
                                        telegram regarding armistice and withdrawal of Chinese
                                        troops from walled city of Nanking. (Signed) Rabe,
                                        Chairman”.</p>
                                </quote></p>
                            <p>2. Sent to Shanghai, repeated to Peiping, Hankow. Nanking please
                                repeat to Tokyo with request that Embassy there communicate to
                                Foreign Office.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>